title: The ToString() method is present on all reference object types. This is due to all reference types being derived from Object which has the ToString() method on it. The ToString() method on the object base class returns the type name. The fragment below will print out “User” to the console.

inline_content.Text: The ToString() method is present on all reference object types. This is due to all reference types being derived from Object which has the ToString() method on it. The ToString() method on the object base class returns the type name. The fragment below will print out “User” to the console.

title: However, the class User can also override ToString() in order to alter the string it returns. The code fragment below prints out “Id: 5, Name: User1” to the console.
